article.headline: Wagner 75, St. Francis, Pa. 58
article.story: NEW YORK -- Chris Martin had 20 points, Llewchean Radford added 15 and Wagner beat St. Francis, Pa. 75-58 on Saturday to snap a six-game losing streak. Martin connected on 6-of-8 from 3-point range and Joey Mundweiler finished with 12 points for the Seahawks (11-12, 4-9 Northeast), who shot 55 percent from the field. Justin Drummond had 10 points, 10 assists and five rebounds. Devin Sweetney had 14 points and 10 rebounds for St. Francis (5-18, 2-10), which has lost 13 of its last 14 games. The Red Flash shot 38.5 percent. Wagner led 42-30 at halftime.
